ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 convertible-bond investors</a>, and even <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/24293736.260983/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMDgvbWljcm9zdHJhdGVneS1ib29zdHMtYml0Y29pbi1saW=
5rZWQtanVuay1ib25kLXRvLTUwMC1taWxsaW9u/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB01c6e70f" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> high-yield=
-bond investors</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0and said =E2=80=9Chey if we wanted to sp=
eculate on Bitcoin would you fund that?=E2=80=9D And the investors were lik=
e, sure, yeah, sounds fun.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a matte=
r of traditional corporate finance it is not at all obvious that you should=
 give some random software company billions of dollars to speculate on Bitc=
oin! You could just speculate on Bitcoin yourself! Or give the money to som=
e Bitcoin-speculating hedge fund that was purposely founded to speculate on=
 Bitcoin![1] But now it doesn=E2=80=99t matter; every company can do whatev=
er it likes and investors will fund it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or =
there is the story of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/24293736.260983/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvZXh4b24tbG9zdC1hLWNsaW1hdGUtcHJveHktZmlnaHQ/607f07ceef4b85=
